// 2. install typeorm to enable communication with db
// 3. npm i typeorm
// 4. npm i bcrypt // dependencies

// ----------------------------------------
// Getting Started with TypeORM:
// Install TypeORM and the database driver for your chosen database (e.g., MySQL, PostgreSQL):

// bash
// Copy code
// npm install typeorm reflect-metadata mysql2
// Replace mysql2 with the appropriate database driver if you're using a different database.

// Setup ormconfig.json: Create a configuration file to define database connection settings:

// json
// Copy code
// {
//   "type": "mysql",
//   "host": "localhost",
//   "port": 3306,
//   "username": "root",
//   "password": "password",
//   "database": "test",
//   "entities": ["src/entity/*.js"],
//   "synchronize": true
// }